    # Calculate the center of the statue patch

query: Are there mirrors to the right of the bus on the road?
generated_code:
# image is a numpy array
    image_patch = ImagePatch(image)
    bus_patches = image_patch.find("bus on the road")
    mirrors = []
    for bus in bus_patches:
        bus_width = bus.width
        bus_height = bus.height
        for i in range(bus.left, image_patch.right):
            mirror = image_patch.crop(i, bus.lower, i + bus_width, bus.upper)
            mirror_width = mirror.width
            mirror_height = mirror.height
            if mirror_height > bus_height:
                mirrors.append(mirror)
    if len(mirrors) > 0:
        return "yes"
    else:
        return "no"  # no mirrors found

query: Is the guy to the right or to the left of the device in the top part of the image?
generated_code:
# this is the API function
    image_patch = ImagePatch(image)
    device_patches = image_patch.find("device")
    device_patch = device_patches[0]
    guy_patches = image_patch.find("guy")
    guy_patches.sort(key=lambda x: x.horizontal_center)
    guy_patch = guy_patches[0]
    guy_left = guy_patch.horizontal_center - guy_patch.width / 2
    guy_right = guy_patch.horizontal_center + guy_patch.width / 2
    guy_up = guy_patch.vertical_center - guy_patch.height / 2
    guy_down = guy_patch.vertical_center + guy_patch.height / 2
    device_up = device_patch.vertical_center - device_patch.height / 2
    device_down = device_patch.vertical_center + device_patch.height / 2
    if guy_left < device_patch.left or guy_right > device_patch.right or guy_up > device_down or guy_down < device_up:
        return "left"
    else:
        return "right"
